cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.CY, cs.SOC, cs.HC

This paper deals with the analysis of social networks and their impact on the well-being of individuals. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also involves the study of complex interactions between individual popularity, happiness, and clustering, which suggests the possibility of it belonging to cs.SD (Software Engineering) or cs.CY (Computers and Society). The paper also discusses the psycho-social effects of social networks, which could place it under cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) or cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
